The pious Trojan , its peculiar Care
The pious Trojan , its peculiar Care , Did numerous Hardships
Neglected lived in some obscure Retreat , And learnt in
Those Springs of Thought , which when they are refined
them the shining Paths of Honour tread , By Praise pushed on
She knew Afflictions , felt a Sister's Hate

Refreshing Breezes faned the balmy Air , The fertile Earth a florid Green did wear : No Clouds obscured the Sun's refulgent Light , He never shone more eminently bright : All things conspired her Welcome to proclaim , Who the Protectress of her People came , By Heaven designed , and her propitious Fate , To be the Bulwark of a tottering State
Who the Protectress of her People came , By Heaven designed , and her propitious Fate , To be the Bulwark of a tottering State
To be the Bulwark of a tottering State

them a Heroin fills the British Throne : A Heroin greater than Romance can frame , And worthy of the Line from whence she came ; In whom the Great and Brave , the Soft and Kind , In One are by the firmest Ties combined : Where nothing's wanting that we can desire , And where we see each Minute something to admire
Her Troops descend with noble Ardour
Way , And from the Dragons snatch the shining Prey : Fame spreads the News through all the encircling Air
spreads the News through all the encircling Air
The drooping Eagles prune their Wings and rise , With joyful Haste they cut the sounding Skies

In sweetest Songs of grateful Praise
, they sing , to give us timely Aid
Be still employed in Service , and in Praise , In glad Attendance , and in grateful Lays
